programme.desc: Danny is asked by the State Vet to help control an outbreak of rabies in the National Park. When Vanessa is concerned for the animals at Mara, Danny assures her it's a long way away and advises her to continue with business as usual.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 1
programme.desc: The Rescue 1 chopper team struggles to save two young men who are feared drowned at Hahei; a Coromandel motorcyclist is struggling with punctured lungs, and young man is trapped inside a car after a high speed accident.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 2
programme.desc: A teenage motorcyclist is fighting for his life after crashing on a remote farm near Warkworth, a man has 2nd degree burns to his face and hands from an accidental explosion, and four men are missing after two boats capsized on the Kawhia bar.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 3
programme.desc: The Rescue 1 team battles to save a man trapped in his overturned Land Rover on Rakino Island; a star rugby player at Onewhero may have broken his neck after a scrum collapsed, and a man out cycling on Waiheke is clinging to life after a cardiac arrest.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 4
programme.desc: The chopper team has an intense struggle to keep a young Waikato woman alive after her car collided with a heavy truck, an 18 year old man is in terrible pain with a dislocated shoulder, and a 9 year old boy is in a bad way after falling out of a tree.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 5
programme.desc: Motorbike rider, Lachlan was testing out his newly designed dirt-bike track when he lost control on a jump. His femur has been badly shattered. The Air Rescue crew is tasked with flying Lachlan to hospital but his medical dramas have only just begun.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 6
programme.desc: Retirees Diane and husband Gary were just a few hours into their Pacific Island cruise of a lifetime when disaster struck. Diane toppled down a set of stairs and now she's in need of urgent medical attention.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 1
programme.desc: A leisure helicopter has gone down in Sydney's Royal National Park with a family of four on board, including three year-old Finn. The stakes are always high when children are involved. The rescue crew locates the crash site but can't get too close.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 2
programme.desc: Three surfing mates go missing in dangerous surf. The massive swell threatens to smash them onto the rocks in Sydney's Lurline Bay. The rescue crew is on a search and rescue mission but there's no sign of the surfer boys.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 3
programme.desc: A monster swell has trapped two teenage girls on the rocks at Sydney's North Head. As high-tide approaches, a daring double-winch rescue is their only option – to stop the teenagers from being swept out to sea.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 5
programme.desc: The Westpac chopper crew attempt to save a Waiheke man who has life-threatening injuries after falling off a ladder and a motocross rider is in a bad way after a 100-foot jump goes badly wrong.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 6
programme.desc: The helicopter rescue crew responds to Pauanui to save a truck driver who's smashed through the windscreen after rolling his truck and a Port Charles family is distraught after a young girl is run over by a quad bike.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 7
programme.desc: The chopper crewmen have their hands full with five badly injured patients after a car crash near Waiuku, and a massive motorcycle pile-up leaves injured bikers all over the road, and a man may have broken his neck after falling from his horse.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 8
programme.desc: As a weather bomb hits, the chopper crew set out on one of the most challenging missions they have ever undertaken 20 miles off shore, a man lays face down at Muriwai beach unable to move.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 9
programme.desc: A hang glider pilot may have broken his back after a heavy crash-landing, a Manaia man is in a bad way after coming off a sea biscuit at high speed, and a crashed Waikato driver needs an urgent air-lift to hospital to save his life.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 4
programme.desc: 55-year-old Gold Coast holidaymaker Irina is in real trouble - she's caught in a deadly ocean rip. Like many tourists, Irena was unaware of the risks of not swimming between the beach flags. The Gold Coast rescue helicopter spots her in the nick of time.

programme.title: 4x4: Fascination offroad
programme.desc: At the All-Wheel Adventure in Bad Kissingen, Germany, the biggest exhibition for offroaders in Europe, we test drove the Rallye Defender and examined how a regular Jeep Wrangler with only a few modifications could double in price.

programme.title: 4x4: All- Wheel- Drive on snow
programme.desc: In winter, when the streets get slippery, an all-wheel drive vehicle brings many advantages as you gain more traction. Under icy conditions we experienced one day in snowy Austria with rally professional Niki Schelle in a Suzuki SX4 S-Cross.

programme.title: 4x4: Rallye Fun
programme.desc: Countryside tours aren't the only option with an all-wheel drive car. You can also have a lot of fun on gravel roads. We show how that goes in a Subaru WRX STI. Also: in the 1990s, Ford had a successful go at international rally competitions...

programme.title: 4x4: All- Wheel- Drive on station wagons
programme.desc: Station wagons are usually regarded as family cars or just vehicles with a lot of cargo hold. But the Skoda Octavia, the Opel Insignia Country Tourer, the Subaru Outback, the Audi S4 allroad quattro and the Seat Leon x-perience want to be more than...
programme.sub-title: All- Wheel- Drive on station wagons

programme.desc: The clients are new, but the spirit is all too familiar as Ryan Buell prepares himself to battle the taunting demon that has been following him.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Dead Legends
programme.desc: PRS and Psychic/Medium Chip Coffey investigate the famed Hotel Conneaut in northern Pennsylvania. Heavy doors opening on their own, sightings of a boy, a bride and a menacing butcher have the hotel's staff on edge.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Shadow Caster
programme.desc: PRS investigates an Alabama home where clients, Georgiana and her two daughters, are so terrified, they moved out after only 18 months. They have seen shadow figures, been touched and have a recorded EVP stating, "Look at me, get out of here."

programme.title: Paranormal State: Satan's Soldier
programme.desc: Mark and Kim can't sleep through the racket caused by unseen forces in their central Indiana home. When PRS and Psychic/Medium Michelle Belanger discover what appears to be blood in the basement, they investigate a history of violence in the home.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Woman in the Window
programme.desc: Ryan and his team lend paranormal assistance to a family who lives in a historic home that was once a part of the Underground Railroad. Does the answer to their haunting lie in the mysterious tunnels beneath the house?

programme.title: Paranormal State: Hide and Seek
programme.desc: Hillary and her nine-year-old son Hunter are being harassed by a shadow presence in their Victorian home in Newburgh, Indiana. Trap doors in the basement reveal artifacts from a bygone era, and the clients have recorded persistent strange noises.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Pet Cemetery
programme.desc: Ryan and his team investigate the bizarre haunting of a woman and her dog in Waterboro, Maine. The Labrador was chewing at her own fur and standing on guard on the bed, growling at unseen figures.

programme.title: Paranormal State: The Sickness
programme.desc: Something is making Lisa and her family sick. Is it natural or paranormal? Ryan and the team uncover the tragic history surrounding Lisa's home--with shocking connections to respiratory illness.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Sixth Sense
programme.desc: A worried mother calls the Paranormal Research Society to help her son Matthew, a boy who sees dead people. Matthew's story strikes a chord with team leader Ryan Buell who also experienced paranormal activity as a child.

programme.title: Paranormal State: I Am Six
programme.desc: Laura has felt oppressed by a violent spirit ever since she heard a chilling EVP in the fall of 2007. The 26-year-old claims she's been beaten, choked, even forcibly submerged.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Shape Shifter
programme.desc: PRS travels to Shapleigh, Maine where a woman and her daughter are reporting attacks from a winged creature with sharp teeth. Psychic Chip Coffey arrives and senses a half-human, half animal presence.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Ghost On the Tracks
programme.desc: PRS is called to a New Jersey beauty salon, but they soon learn that the building's proximity to deadly train tracks might be the true cause of spirit activity.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Permission To Do Harm
programme.desc: When a mirror levitates and shatters on its own, P.R.S. heeds the call to investigate a spirit that has been unleashed on an unsuspecting family. Ryan must track down the spirit and contain it before it does irreparable damage.

programme.title: Paranormal State: The Fury
programme.desc: Kathy, her two daughters and her new husband, "Farmer" thought they had the perfect, quiet life deep in the mountains of West Virginia.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Oxford Castle Unlocked
programme.desc: The team investigate Oxford Castle Unlocked, a tourist attraction based on the site of a former prison complex. With such a brutal history, it is said to be rife with paranormal activity.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Chislehurst Caves - Part Two
programme.desc: Violence and the threat of human sacrifice disturb guest medium Brian Shepherd and the "Most Haunted" team as they continue their investigation into the spooky happenings at the Chislehurst Caves.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Hack Green Bunker
programme.desc: Yvette and the "Most Haunted" team travel to Cheshire to investigate Hack Green Nuclear Bunker, discovering an illicit wartime love affair and tales of tortured spies.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Nunnington Hall
programme.desc: The "Most Haunted" team investigates Nunnington Hall. Dating from the 13th century, all the rooms seem to have ghost or psychic manifestations. Will the team be able to bring these spirits to light?

programme.title: Most Haunted: The Exeter Old Courts
programme.desc: The team investigates the Exeter Old Courts in Devon, where many people have been sentenced to death. The last hanging for witchcraft took place here during the infamous Bideford witch trial.

programme.title: Most Haunted: The Niddry Street Vaults
programme.desc: The team investigates the Niddry Street Vaults where witches, poltergeists and an evil misogynist await. The damp and dirty walls hold a myriad supernatural occurrences that defy explanation.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Jedburgh Castle
programme.desc: The team investigates Jedburgh Castle, an Industrial Revolution-era prison at the center of many stories of strange sightings, odd happenings and reports of phantom pipe music heard at night.

programme.title: Most Haunted: S.S. Great Britain
programme.desc: The team explores the S.S. Great Britain, the largest and strongest ship ever built. Stories of hauntings and the chance to be the first to carry out a paranormal investigation here spur the crew on.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Hello and Farewell - Part 1
programme.desc: Jonathan helps Commander Michaels to deal with flashbacks of Vietnam; he also tries to convince her to go to therapy. Mark deals with his fear of flying.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: The Silent Bell
programme.desc: A pastor must follow a church council's decision to fire most of the staff at the school because they're not Christian.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: The Reunion
programme.desc: Mark attends his high school class reunion and learns that some memories are bittersweet for his old friends.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: The Source
programme.desc: A teenage girl tells school reporters that a driver came on to her right before the bus got into an accident. She may not be telling the truth. Jonathan tries to teach the news writers the correct way to report a story.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven
programme.desc: The problems of the handicapped are addressed when an amputee joins a crusade after a false fire alarm.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Goodbye, Mr. Zelinka
programme.desc: Mr. Zelinka is a beloved teacher who is being forced to retire because he's old. Jonathan and Mark know that he would prefer to continue teaching.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Choices
programme.desc: The parents of two Vietnamese children come to America to look for them after a ten-year separation.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Summer Camp
programme.desc: After having been scarred in a fire, an actress becomes a counselor at a summer camp for blind children. The camp is run by Jonathan and Mark's blind friend Frank.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: From Hard Hat to Hottie
programme.desc: Laura is a former construction worker who spent years exposed to the harsh elements. Our whole team of experts has kicked into gear to turn back the clock and transform this former construction worker from hard hat to hottie.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: I'm No Grandma
programme.desc: Kathy is a mother who has battled health setbacks while raising her kids. She wants to shake off her general malaise and look better as a first step to feeling better. Find out how Kathy goes from dreary to cheery in her journey to look ten years younger.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Self Conscious To Self Confident
programme.desc: Laura, a public speaker, has lost her self-confidence and is now only self-conscious. Once upbeat and bubbly, she suffered from an illness that took its toll on her appearance and self esteem. Can our experts help Laura regain her identity and a new look?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Jilly Graham
programme.desc: Nicky Hambleton-Jones and her team of age-busting experts come to the rescue of Jilly Graham from Bradford.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Soccer Mom to Soccer Bomb!
programme.desc: Colleen Radcliffe is a mother of four and says she doesn't have a spare second to spend on herself. Colleen feels like the old mom with no end in sight, but we're here to teach her that isn't the case. Time to make Colleen look 10 Years Younger!

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Photo-phobic To Photogenic
programme.desc: After a rough divorce, Alison has became a single mom. The stress of being the sole breadwinner has left its mark. Will the experts be able to give Alison back her youthful glow?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Spinning a More Youthful Look
programme.desc: Evan is a mobile DJ who is trying to take his business to the next level. Evan hasn't had the time or money to take care his looks but he knows it's absolutely necessary now if his business is going to continue growing.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Getting Back on the Catwalk
programme.desc: Stacey is a former model whose appearance has gone downhill because of the demands of caring for both her new baby and her ill mother. She's eager to get back on the catwalk and our team of experts will do a head to toe transformation.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Ronnie Donno
programme.desc: Teaching assistant Ronnie Donno already feels bad about the way she looks but before work can begin on getting her to look younger she has to hear how old 100 members of the public think she looks.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Jackie Ralph
programme.desc: Inside, Jackie Ralph still feels like a flirty young woman. Only problem is, she's trapped inside the body of a 61 year old – at least that's what the British public think. Nicky Hambleton Jones and her team of experts take charge.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Beauty is More Than Skin Deep
programme.desc: Tracy is a dedicated single mom, and a survivor. After devastating cystic acne scarred her face, she suffered a terrible oven accident that left her with even more scars. Our team of experts, and The Glam Squad, give Tracy the TLC she deserves
programme.sub-title: Beauty is More Than Skin Deep

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Polishing the Prize
programme.desc: Ellisa is a recent newlywed whose life hasn't felt much like a honeymoon since her husband is always on the road for work and she is left at home with a new baby! Fearing that her husband could stray while away, our team of experts help Ellisa.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger New Zealand
programme.desc: Everyone wants to look younger but if you work hard and play hard like Sue Whyte, it's far tougher to roll back those years. Sue's already stopped smoking and lost a lot of weight so can Fiona McDonald and her team of time warriors take care of the rest?

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 3
programme.desc: Danny is asked by the State Vet to help control an outbreak of rabies in the National Park. When Vanessa is concerned for the animals at Mara, Danny assures her it's a long way away and advises her to continue with business as usual.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 4
programme.desc: It's the day before Rosie's wedding. Danny is proud of his daughter and determined to feed her up now that she's eating for two. All the family are excited about the imminent return of Caroline, especially Du Plessis who can't wait to see his fiancé.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 5
programme.desc: Alice and Danny are called out by a farmer who's trapped an African Wild Dog. As they're even more endangered than cheetahs and much more vicious, Danny and Alice are amazed to see one up close.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 6
programme.desc: When Du Plessis instructs the family to be around for dinner, they are intrigued to hear he's planning a big announcement. However, he won't be drawn on details and tells them to be patient.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 7
programme.desc: Alice and Danny are delighted when the Animal Hospital is given responsibility for the rescue and conservation of animals in the region – it's a big achievement after all their hard work.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 8
programme.desc: Danny and Alice are concerned about a missing male giraffe but Du Plessis is confident he can find him. He's as good as his word but they're upset to discover Mara lions have killed the giraffe.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 9
programme.desc: The family frantically dig for Charlotte in the rubble, hoping that somehow she has survived. Rowan arrives and takes charge of the situation, directing them to be more methodical in their rescue efforts.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 10
programme.desc: Danny and Alice are enjoying being together but agree to keep their relationship under wraps for the moment. However, they're unaware Georgina has heard their every word!

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 4
programme.desc: 55-year-old Gold Coast holidaymaker Irina is in real trouble - she's caught in a deadly ocean rip. Like many tourists, Irena was unaware of the risks of not swimming between the beach flags. The Gold Coast rescue helicopter spots her in the nick of time.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 5
programme.desc: A head-on car collision in Tasmania has left tourists Hong and Xeu Wu fighting for their lives. Ambulance crews have managed to stabilize Mr. Wu but Mrs. Wu is in a critical condition and calling out for her husband.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 6
programme.desc: A team of amateur scuba divers find themselves in deep trouble when their boat capsizes off Sydney's Botany Bay. The Westpac La Perouse crew spots the distressed divers while on a routine training mission.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 1
programme.desc: 65-year old Dave, a surf skier, is attacked and bitten by a Great White shark while training in the ocean. Dehydrated (after four days at sea), Margo needs urgent hospital care.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 2
programme.desc: A car crashes another car at a country intersection. It's situation critical with four people trapped. It turns out someone was running from the police – and he was on drugs.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 10
programme.desc: A motocross rider may have broken his back after hitting a tree head on at high speed, at a sawmill a man faces its worse nightmares; and a woman is fighting for her life after taking an accidental overdose of her husband's medication.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 1
programme.desc: Auckland's Westpac helicopter crew races to save two teenage girls fighting for their lives after their car crashed and rolled the Waiwera Hill.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 2
programme.desc: Professional scuba diver Brian Green has been found floating and not breathing, and is on a boat near the Noises, a group of islands in the Hauraki Gulf. The team has to move fast.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 3
programme.desc: On Great Mercury Island near Coromandel, a scuba diver has surfaced unconscious without a pulse. Without Rescue 1 he may soon be dead.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 4
programme.desc: The Rescue 1 team respond to a call out where an elderly couple in their 60s are in a critical condition after a head on collision.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 3
programme.desc: Tasmania Police is on high alert after a prisoner escapes from jail. The man is armed and dangerous. The Rescue Helicopter is called in to assist with the manhunt. Things turn deadly when they spot him.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 4
programme.desc: Hiker Robert had trained for over 6 months for the remote Cradle Mountain bush walk. With his young daughter in tow they set off on a 48 km walk. Three hours into the walk Roberts health takes a turn for the worse.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 5
programme.desc: A young man has flipped his quad bike and can't move his neck. Later that night, the crew is called to a suburban house because a DIY homebuilder has fallen through the roof in his house – and there's a bone sticking out through his jeans.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 6
programme.desc: De Anna and her husband were celebrating their 50th wedding anniversary on board a luxury liner. The ship's doctor radios for help. But the liner is a long way out at sea. Can the rescue crew get to De Anna in time?

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 1
programme.desc: 14 year-old motor-cross rider, Kacee gets the death wobbles and cartwheels over the top of his handle bars and hits the ground head first. He's now struggling to breath and is barely able to talk. Team Air Rescue needs to get Kacee to the hospital fast.

programme.desc: The Pikes Peak Hill Climb is a rather different type of race in the mountains of Colorado, USA. It's unique, fascinating and full of adventure. One of the starters at the 1987 Pikes Peak is two-time rally world champion Walter Röhrl.

programme.title: Classic Races: Grand Prix Races since 1934
programme.desc: Since 1934 the Grand Prix has been the most exciting and fascinating world championship in the world. With its state-of-the-art vehicles featuring horsepower from the biggest brands, it never fails to wow its viewers.

programme.title: Classic Races: Rallye Year 1972 - A Ford Success Story
programme.desc: The international championship for manufacturers was a rally series which ran from 1970 to 1972. Car manufacturers such as Porsche, Renault and Ford all took part, with Ford having an exceptionally successful year in 1972.
programme.sub-title: Rallye Year 1972 - A Ford Success Story

programme.title: Classic Races: German Touring Championship 1992

programme.title: Classic Races: Touring Car Grand Prix, Argentina 1964
programme.desc: Tropical temperatures, never-ending dust and curves: those are just some of the many difficulties for man and machine during the 1964 Grand Prix in Argentina. This race was responsible for taking the Mercedes brand to the top.

programme.title: Classic Races: Indy 500 1994
programme.desc: The Indy 500 is one of the world's most spectacular motor races in the world. Watched by a huge number of people, this motorsports event doesn't fail to impress at the Indianapolis Motor Speedway.

programme.title: Classic Races: German Rallye Championship 1983
programme.desc: The German rally championship is one of the most popular motorsport series and has been running since 1970. At the 1983 race, the sporty models from Opel saw exceptional success.

programme.title: Classic Races: Quattro The New Dimension 1985
programme.desc: With the introduction of the Group D-Monsters in the World Rally Championships, the fight for the title got harder and harder. Thats why Audi brought a strong trump onto the road in 1985 - The Sport Quattro. And with it began a new dimension.

programme.title: Classic Races: The Rallye World Championship 1982
programme.desc: The African continent is always a difficult terrain for rally drivers. That wasn't any different for the 1982 World Rally Championship, when heat, dust, mud and hardly passable routes posed major challenges for drivers, co-drivers and engines.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: First of its Kind

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Knock Knock

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Poker Face

programme.title: Homicide Hunter

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Time Bomb

programme.desc: A Hollywood couple had to turn down work because their French bulldog failed the Doggy Daycare entrance exam. Three Jack Russells began to fight each other when their owner got a serious boyfriend.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Cobar and Chase
programme.desc: Cesar takes a trip to Australia to help Cobar, a Koolie with a fear of squeaky toys. Then, he steps through the looking glass to help a Shar-pei mix who lunges at his own reflection in mirrors.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Jonbee, Hudson & Violet, and Buford
programme.desc: A ferocious stray Jindo in desperate need of rescue, a Great Dane wreaks havoc on house and home, a boxer mourns the death of a beloved mate.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Fear of Dogs

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Jake in Exile

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: My Strange Addiction Special 2
programme.desc: In this one-hour special, we revisit six of our addicts whose stories shocked the world. Tune in for exclusive never before seen footage in this special episode.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Drinks Nail Polish & Ear Digger
programme.desc: Bertha has been drinking up to five bottles of nail polish every day for the past five years but her family is worried she's doing permanent damage to her health. Jamie can't stop digging in her ears.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Dating My Car/ Baby Powder Addict
programme.desc: Nathaniel has been in a relationship with his car for nearly five years, taking it out on dates, buying it gifts, and even getting intimate with it. Jaye has been addicted to snorting baby powder.
programme.sub-title: Dating My Car/ Baby Powder Addict

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Addicted to My Breasts/Tape Eater
programme.desc: Sheyla has spent $250,000 on 22 breast enlargement surgeries to achieve her 38KKK bust size, despite suffering a severe infection from her recent implants. Andrea is addicted to eating adhesive tape.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Eats Dirt/Extreme Toenails
programme.desc: Kristie has eaten dirt every day for the last 30 years, consuming more than five tons since her addiction began. Meanwhile, Ayanna is addicted to growing her toenails.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Addicted to Coffee Enemas/Licks Cats
programme.desc: Trina and her husband Mike have done nearly 7,000 coffee enemas over the last two and a half years. Lisa has been addicted to licking her cat and eating clumps of its hair for three years.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Extreme Hair/Addicted to Bee Stings
programme.desc: Asha hasn't cut her 21-foot long hair in nearly a quarter century and spends up to six hours a day grooming her ten-pound locks. Margaret has stung herself over 50,000 times with bees.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Addicted to Inflatables/Butt Injection Addict
programme.desc: Mark has been addicted to his 15 inflatable pool toys, eating with them, sleeping with them and even bathing them. Karmello has been getting black market butt injections for the last three years.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Identical Twin Obsession / Eats Mattresses
programme.desc: Twins Amy and Becky are addicted to being identical, looking alike, acting alike, and even weighing their meals to stay the same size. Jennifer is addicted to eating mattresses.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Addicted to a Doll/Eats Plastic Bags
programme.desc: Robert, a 23-year-old man who's addicted to eating plastic newspaper bags, an addition so intense, that he goes days without food. Catherine, a 48-year-old woman whose best friend is a doll.
programme.sub-title: Addicted to a Doll/Eats Plastic Bags

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Casting / Psychics
programme.desc: Profiled are Kevin, who constantly covers his body in plaster casts even though he is not injured, and Melissa who is incapable of making a decision without a consulting a psychic.

programme.title: My Crazy Obsession: My Crazy Obsession Pilot
programme.desc: My Collection Obsession takes you deep inside the world of four of the country’s most obsessed collectors each taking their material obsession to jaw-dropping extremes.

programme.title: My Crazy Obsession: 5,000 Kids_Tickled Pink
programme.desc: Pat and Joe are passionate about their extreme collection of over 5,000 infamous kid dolls. Kitty Kay Sera is completely obsessed with the color pink. She even wears pink clothes and eats pink food.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Floating for a Bargain
programme.desc: Mac and his wife, Kelsey, are looking for a home for them and their 5-month-old daughter on the tubing paradise, the Bogue Chitto River.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Gator Island
programme.desc: Alligator Point, Florida is so swampy and wild, it’s known as the Forgotten Coast. This area feels more bayou than tropical, which is exactly why water taxi driver Richard and Julia want a waterfront home here.

programme.title: Buying Hawaii: Off the Base
programme.desc: There’s a lot of pressure living life on a submarine—that’s why Naval Officer Jeremy Brown and his wife, Nikki, want to move out of Pearl Harbor and into the lush Hawaiian Mountains.

programme.title: Buying Hawaii: Turnin’ Up The Heat
programme.desc: Maui is where people come to escape. That’s exactly why Patrick and Jeannie came here from cold Massachusetts.They want to upgrade their condo for their own piece of Maui.

programme.title: Buying Hawaii: Jungle Fever
programme.desc: Maui’s filled with deserts by the coast and lush jungles in the mountains, many people come here to escape. Jeff and Pam want to get away from the desert and into the jungle, but will it be too wild?

programme.title: Buying Hawaii: Flying Kauai
programme.desc: Gerry and Julie moved to Kauai searching for adventure. Gerry is a pilot and hang glider; he would love to find a property where he can fuse his love of excitement with functional living.

programme.title: Buying Hawaii: Backyard Survival
programme.desc: Life on Oahu is so expensive, for some families, the only way to get by is to grow your own food. That’s what Erik and Amy Eck want, a backyard farm to teach their baby, how to live off the land.

programme.title: Buying Hawaii: Volcano Living
programme.desc: The Big Island is the only place in Hawaii you’ll find active volcanoes. No matter where you are, you’re in the path of lava. Joel and Lani are willing to take the risk, but how close will they get?

programme.title: Buying Hawaii: Big Island Project
programme.desc: Jesse and his wife Tracy have been living in a tent on the Big Island for three years. They’re ready to upgrade their lifestyle but still looking for a house where they can still live off the grid.

programme.title: Buying Hawaii: Big Apple to Big Island
programme.desc: DeVante’s making the move from the Big Apple to the Big Island. But for he and his girlfriend, Jen, life out here is way different than they imagined – there’s volcanoes, tsunamis, even giant bugs.

programme.title: Buying Hawaii: Boar Island
programme.desc: Martin and Connie came to Kauai from Los Angeles. Between the constant rain, sea creatures, and wild boars, life is rustic, but they’re here to stay, and want the perfect home for their adventure.

programme.title: Buying Hawaii: One Way Ticket
programme.desc: Many people dream of living in Hawaii, and Tucker and Nicole have made that dream a reality. After huge life events, they bought one-way tickets to Oahu and are looking to put down permanent roots.

programme.title: Buying Log Cabins: Million Dollar Log Castles - THE RISKEVICH’S Minnesota
programme.desc: Kevin and Jennifer are escaping city life and looking at three one-of-a-kind log mansions. Homes offer the best views and some unique features that only Northern Minnesotans will need!
programme.sub-title: Million Dollar Log Castles - THE RISKEVICH’S Minnesota

programme.title: Buying Log Cabins: Mountain Homes - THE EMBLER’S - COLORADO
programme.desc: Matt and Genevieve are newlyweds looking to purchase their first home and they want a log cabin. They look at three different cabins offering amazing options.
